### 🚀 PILLAR 2 — EXTREME PERFORMANCE ENGINEERING

#### 2.1 Database Query Optimization — The Big 5

**a) Full-Text Search with `tsvector`** — Replace your `ILIKE '%term%'` global search (full table scan every time):
```sql
-- Migration: Add GIN index for full-text search
ALTER TABLE services ADD COLUMN search_vector tsvector 
  GENERATED ALWAYS AS (to_tsvector('arabic', title || ' ' || COALESCE(description,''))) STORED;
CREATE INDEX idx_services_fts ON services USING GIN(search_vector);

-- New query (100x faster)
SELECT * FROM services WHERE search_vector @@ plainto_tsquery('arabic', $1);
```

**b) Partial Indexes** — Your admin queries filter by `status` constantly:
```sql
CREATE INDEX idx_orders_pending ON orders(created_at DESC) WHERE status = 'pending';
CREATE INDEX idx_contacts_new ON contacts(created_at DESC) WHERE status = 'new';
CREATE INDEX idx_users_active ON users(email) WHERE is_active = TRUE AND is_verified = TRUE;
```

**c) Materialized Views for Admin Dashboard** — Your [getStats](file:///e:/Roya/server/controllers/admin.controller.js#7-56) fires 9 parallel queries. Replace with one:
```sql
CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW admin_dashboard_stats AS
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) as total_users,
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders) as total_orders,
  (SELECT COALESCE(SUM(price),0) FROM orders WHERE status='completed') as total_revenue,
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders WHERE status='pending') as pending_orders,
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM contacts WHERE status='new') as unanswered_messages;
-- Refresh every 5 minutes via cron/BullMQ
```

**d) JSON Aggregation** — Stop N+1 queries in controllers:
```sql
-- Instead of fetching orders then looping for user data:
SELECT o.*, row_to_json(u) as user_data 
FROM orders o 
LEFT JOIN users u ON o.user_id = u.id
WHERE o.status = $1
ORDER BY o.created_at DESC;
```

**e) Read Replicas** — All `GET` requests go to a read replica; only writes go to primary. Your existing `query()` function in `config/database.js` gets an optional `{ useReplica: true }` flag.

#### 2.2 HTTP/2 Server Push + Asset Optimization
```js
// Preload critical CSS/JS in HTML <head>
<link rel="preload" href="/css/main.css" as="style">
<link rel="preload" href="/js/auth.js" as="script">
```

Add `<link rel="dns-prefetch">` for Cloudinary, Google Fonts, and CDN domains already in your CSP.

#### 2.3 Image Pipeline Upgrade
Currently you upload to Cloudinary but deliver raw URLs. Add **on-the-fly transformations**:
```js
// Instead of: https://res.cloudinary.com/roya/image/upload/photo.jpg
// Serve:      https://res.cloudinary.com/roya/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto,w_800/photo.jpg
//             ↑ auto WebP/AVIF conversion    ↑ smart quality  ↑ responsive width

// In upload.service.js — store the public_id, not the full URL
// Generate optimized URLs at render time via Nunjucks filter:
nunjucks.addFilter('cloudimg', (publicId, width = 800) =>
  `https://res.cloudinary.com/${config.cloudinary.cloudName}/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto,w_${width}/${publicId}`
);
```

