### ⚙️ PILLAR 7 — ASYNC JOB QUEUE ENGINE

**The Problem:** Your `emailService.sendOTP()`, `emailService.sendInvoice()`, [pdf.service.js](file:///e:/Roya/server/services/pdf.service.js), and [whatsapp.service.js](file:///e:/Roya/server/services/whatsapp.service.js) all run **synchronously inside the HTTP request lifecycle**. If Nodemailer is slow (2-3 seconds), your user waits. If it fails, the error bubbles up inside the controller. **This is a ticking bomb.**

#### 7.1 BullMQ — Enterprise Job Queue
```bash
npm install bullmq
```

```js
// server/queues/email.queue.js
const { Queue, Worker } = require('bullmq');
const redis = require('../config/redis');

const emailQueue = new Queue('emails', { connection: redis });

// In auth.controller.js register():
// BEFORE: await emailService.sendOTP(user.email, user.name, otp);
// AFTER:
await emailQueue.add('send-otp', { to: user.email, name: user.name, otp }, {
  attempts: 3,
  backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 1000 },
  removeOnComplete: 100,
  removeOnFail: 500,
});
// Response returns instantly. Email sends in background.

// Worker (runs in separate process):
const emailWorker = new Worker('emails', async (job) => {
  if (job.name === 'send-otp') await emailService.sendOTP(job.data.to, job.data.name, job.data.otp);
  if (job.name === 'send-invoice') await emailService.sendInvoice(job.data.to, job.data.name, job.data.number, job.data.pdf);
  if (job.name === 'send-whatsapp') await whatsappService.sendMessage(job.data.phone, job.data.message);
}, { connection: redis, concurrency: 5 });
```

Jobs for the queue:
- `email:otp` — register/resend
- `email:reset` — password reset
- `email:invoice` — order confirmed
- `email:contact-reply` — admin reply
- `whatsapp:order-confirmed` — **finally activate your stub!**
- `pdf:generate` — async invoice PDF generation
- `stats:refresh-materialized-view` — scheduled every 5min

