### 🎨 PILLAR 9 — UX/UI PERFECTION

#### 9.1 Progressive Web App (PWA)
```js
// client/js/sw.js — Service Worker
const CACHE_NAME = 'roya-v1';
const STATIC_ASSETS = ['/css/main.css', '/js/auth.js', '/js/utils.js', '/images/logo.svg'];

self.addEventListener('install', e => {
  e.waitUntil(caches.open(CACHE_NAME).then(c => c.addAll(STATIC_ASSETS)));
});

// Stale-while-revalidate for pages
self.addEventListener('fetch', e => {
  if (e.request.mode === 'navigate') {
    e.respondWith(fetch(e.request).catch(() => caches.match('/offline.html')));
  }
});
```
Add `manifest.json` with app icon, theme color, and `display: standalone`. Users can **install Roya as a native app** from their browser — no App Store required.

#### 9.2 Web Push Notifications
```bash
npm install web-push
```
```js
// server/services/push.service.js
webpush.setVapidDetails('mailto:support@roya.com', config.push.publicKey, config.push.privateKey);
const sendPush = async (subscription, payload) => webpush.sendNotification(subscription, JSON.stringify(payload));
```
When an order status changes with your WebSocket in Pillar 4, also send a Web Push notification. **Users get notified even when the tab is closed.**

#### 9.3 Advanced Dashboard UX — Data Visualization
Upgrade [admin.js](file:///e:/Roya/server/seed-admin.js) from counting stats to **time-series charts** using ApexCharts (already in your CSP):
```js
// Revenue trend: 30-day rolling window
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', created_at) as day, SUM(price) as revenue
FROM orders WHERE status='completed' AND created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'
GROUP BY day ORDER BY day;

// User registration growth curve
// Order funnel: pending → confirmed → in_progress → completed → % drop-off at each stage
// Geographic heat map of property inquiries by governorate
```

#### 9.4 Skeleton Loading States
Replace JavaScript `loading: true` spinners with CSS skeleton loaders that match the shape of actual content. This is the single biggest perceived performance improvement — pages feel instant even before data arrives.

#### 9.5 Keyboard Navigation & Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- All modals trap focus (`Tab`/`Shift+Tab` cycles within modal)
- `aria-live` regions for toast notifications
- `aria-label` on all icon-only buttons  
- `prefers-reduced-motion` media query to disable animations for users with vestibular disorders
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 everywhere

---

### 📱 PILLAR 10 — MOBILE-FIRST EXPANSION

#### 10.1 REST API Hardening for Mobile Clients
Your API currently returns inconsistent response shapes. Standardize completely:
```js
// server/utils/response.js
const ok = (res, data, meta = {}) => res.json({ success: true, data, meta, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
const err = (res, message, code, status = 400) => res.status(status).json({ success: false, error: { code, message }, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
```

#### 10.2 React Native / Expo Mobile App
Your Express API is already the perfect backend. A React Native Expo app that consumes it:
- Property listings with map view (Google Maps integration)
- Push notifications via Expo Push Service
- Photo uploads directly to Cloudinary from phone
- Authenticated via your existing JWT cookie system (switch to `Authorization: Bearer` header for mobile)
- **Time to MVP: 3 weeks** using Expo Router + React Query

#### 10.3 WhatsApp Business API — Finally Activate the Stub
```js
// server/services/whatsapp.service.js — replace the stub
const sendMessage = async (phone, message, templateName = null) => {
  const payload = templateName
    ? { type: 'template', template: { name: templateName, language: { code: 'ar' } } }
    : { type: 'text', text: { body: message } };
  
  const response = await fetch(`https://graph.facebook.com/v18.0/${config.whatsapp.phoneNumberId}/messages`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${config.whatsapp.token}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({ messaging_product: 'whatsapp', to: phone, ...payload }),
  });
  return response.json();
};
```
Use **Meta WhatsApp Cloud API** (free tier, no Twilio needed). Templates for: order confirmation, password reset, invoice ready, inquiry follow-up.

